<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">
<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">
<p style="margin: 0px;">The Senior Manager, Development for the Americas Utility Power Plant Group will be responsible for managing the real estate, permitting and interconnection aspects of multiple utility and commercial scale PV projects in California and Nevada.&nbsp; This cross functional position will be responsible for all phases of the projects&rsquo; life cycle, including prospecting, site identification, site acquisition, mid- and late-stage development, and support of project financing and closing of transactions.</p><p style="margin: 0px;">&nbsp;</p><p style="margin: 0px;">This is a new position at SunPower. It will report to the Director of Development, West Region.</p><p style="margin: 0px;">&nbsp;</p><p style="margin: 0px;">Essential duties and responsibilities include the following.&nbsp; Other duties may be assigned:&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Managing the interconnection, real estate and permitting aspects of multiple utility and commercial scale projects from approximately 20MW in size and up</li><li>Working very cross-functionally with other departments involved in the overall advancement of projects including Origination, Engineering, Construction, Legal, Accounting and Finance teams</li><li>Supporting M&amp;A and project financing activities at various stages of the project lifecycle</li><li>Leading the due diligence and fatal flaw analysis of potential project acquisitions</li><li>Incorporating the input of subject matter experts, including those with expertise in real estate, permitting and interconnection. At times, playing a lead role in real estate, permitting and interconnection activities</li><li>Identifying and managing relationships with consultants and external legal counsel</li><li>Representing SunPower with external project stakeholders including landowners, permitting agencies, transmission providers, and at public hearings and government and community events</li><li>Supporting the submittal of origination proposals to customers and partners</li></ul>
<div id="iCIMS_Expandable_Button"></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>



<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">
Minimum Requirements:
</div>
<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job" itemprop="qualifications">
<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">
<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">
<ul><li><p style="margin: 0px;"><strong>Education and Experience:</strong></p><ul><li>8+ years&rsquo; experience in:<ul><li>the renewable energy electric industry,</li><li>Renewable Energy project development, including permitting, real estate, and transmission,</li><li>Managing multidisciplinary development projects</li></ul></li><li>Experience developing renewable energy projects through project financing and closing of transactions</li><li>Strong track record of managing large interdisciplinary projects</li><li>Network of consultants and other professional relationships to support SunPower in-house development efforts</li><li>Experience working with project stakeholders and in public environments</li><li>Experience presenting project development proposals and activities to senior management</li><li>Fluency in MS Excel, PowerPoint, and Word</li></ul><p style="margin: 0px;">&nbsp;</p><p style="margin: 0px;"><strong>Skills and Qualifications:</strong></p><p style="margin: 0px;">&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Tenacious problem solver &ndash; able to accurately assess, solve, implement, and communicate solutions to problems</li><li>Proven ability to adapt to change in a calm and measured manner</li><li>Proven project manager with demonstrated execution experience and people management skills</li><li>Highly effective communicator -- able to craft and present excellent written presentations and analyze data to support arguments.</li><li>Skilled at creating, summarizing and presenting information logically, for executive decision-making</li><li>Strong leadership and strategic skills with an ability to balance and prioritize competing interests</li><li>Demonstrated ability to develop new business relationships quickly and to close business</li><li>Demonstrated ability to work effectively in a fast-paced, dynamic environment</li><li>Demonstrated ability to manage and interface effectively with cross-functional employee groups of all levels and competencies</li><li>Ability to perform and interpret financial analysis and provide appropriate data and information</li><li>Excellent oral and written communication and presentation skills</li><li>Excellent interpersonal and time management skills</li><li>Entrepreneurial, self-starter with a burning desire to learn and win</li></ul></li></ul>
